The rolling file appender uses the timezone in your `%d{...}` pattern to determine, when the day ends. The general form of the date pattern is:
```
%d{format specifiers}{timezone}
```

If the `timezone` parameter is missing, it defaults to the system timezone.

If you want to rotate base on UTC, just change:
```lang-xml
&lt;RollingFile name=&quot;rollingFile&quot;
             fileName=&quot;${log_path}/solr_data_uploader.log&quot;
             filePattern=&quot;${log_path}/solr_data_uploader-%d{yyyy-MM-dd}.log.gz&quot;&gt;
```
to
```lang-xml
&lt;RollingFile name=&quot;rollingFile&quot;
             fileName=&quot;${log_path}/solr_data_uploader.log&quot;
             filePattern=&quot;${log_path}/solr_data_uploader-%d{yyyy-MM-dd}{UTC}.log.gz&quot;&gt;
```

